2. Difference between an id and class in HTML?
  -- HTML id Attribute: The id attribute is a unique identifier which is used to specify the document. It is used by CSS and JavaScript to perform 
     a certain task for a unique element. In CSS, the id attribute is written using # symbol followed by id.
     
  -- HTML class Attribute: The class attribute is used to specify one or more class names for an HTML element. The class attribute can be used on
    any HTML element. The class name can be used by CSS and JavaScript to perform certain tasks for elements with the specified class name. 
    The class name in CSS stylesheet using “.” symbol.
    
  -- Difference between id and class attribute: The only difference between them is that “id” is unique in a page and can only apply to at
    most one element, while “class” selector can apply to multiple elements. 
    
